{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "Tachi",
          "semanticVersion": "1.8",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/davidmatousek/tachi",
          "supportedTaxonomies": [
            { "name": "OWASP", "index": 0 },
            { "name": "CWE", "index": 1 }
          ],
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Identity spoofing threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker assumes the identity of another user, service, or component to gain unauthorized access or bypass authentication controls." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authentication mechanisms at all trust boundaries. Verify mTLS, signed tokens, and session binding controls.",
                "markdown": "Review authentication mechanisms at all trust boundaries.\n\n**References**: OWASP A07 (Identification and Authentication Failures), CWE-287 (Improper Authentication)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "authentication", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A07", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-287", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/tampering",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Data tampering threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker modifies data in transit, at rest, or in processing — including configuration, persona state, and audit log records." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review integrity controls on all data flows, stored data, and inter-process messages. Verify digital signatures, hash verification, and write-access controls.",
                "markdown": "Review integrity controls on all data flows.\n\n**References**: OWASP A08 (Software and Data Integrity Failures), CWE-345 (Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "tampering", "integrity", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A08", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-345", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Repudiation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an actor denies having performed an action, or where the system cannot prove that a specific action occurred — especially critical for AI agent emissions and user dialogue." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review audit logging completeness and tamper-evidence. Verify that all agent actions are logged with content hashes and signed timestamps.",
                "markdown": "Review audit logging completeness.\n\n**References**: OWASP A09 (Security Logging and Monitoring Failures), CWE-778 (Insufficient Logging)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "repudiation", "logging", "audit", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A09", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-778", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Information disclosure threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where sensitive data — including system prompts, persona state, conversation history, or user disclosures — is exposed to unauthorized parties." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review access controls on all data stores and output paths. Verify output scrubbing, field-level log classification, and per-user session isolation.",
                "markdown": "Review access controls on data stores and outputs.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control), CWE-200 (Exposure of Sensitive Information)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "information-disclosure", "data-exposure", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-200", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Denial of service threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker exhausts resources, disrupts service, or denies legitimate users access — including resource exhaustion attacks on AI inference and storage backends." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review rate limiting, resource quotas, and circuit breakers. Verify capacity planning and DDoS mitigation at trust boundaries.",
                "markdown": "Review availability controls.\n\n**References**: OWASP A04 (Insecure Design), CWE-693 (Protection Mechanism Failure)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "denial-of-service", "availability", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A04", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-693", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/elevation-of-privilege",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Privilege escalation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker gains capabilities or access beyond their authorization — including prompt injection enabling agent self-authorization and persona-prompt manipulation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authorization enforcement at all components. Verify per-session scoped permissions, zero-trust execution context, and persona-prompt validation.",
                "markdown": "Review authorization enforcement.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control), CWE-269 (Improper Privilege Management)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "elevation-of-privilege", "authorization", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-269", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "AI agent autonomy and trust-exploitation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats specific to AI agent frameworks — including agent autonomy boundary violations (ASI-01), tool-abuse (MCP-03/ASI-07), and human-trust-exploitation on consumer-facing AI Processes (OWASP ASI09:2026). The TE-{N} sub-class covers undisclosed AI authorship, authority-claim emission without confidence/source attestation, persuasive-tone manipulation, persona-boundary violations, and synthetic-relationship exploitation in vulnerable-population contexts." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review agent scope enforcement, AI-disclosure mechanisms, confidence/source attestation, persuasion classifiers, persona discipline, and vulnerable-population safeguards.",
                "markdown": "Review agent scope and consumer-protection controls.\n\n**References**: OWASP Agentic Security Initiative (ASI-01, ASI-07, ASI09:2026), MCP Top 10 (MCP-03), CWE-223 (Omission of Security-relevant Information), CWE-287 (Improper Authentication), CWE-290 (Authentication Bypass by Spoofing), CWE-345 (Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity), CWE-693 (Protection Mechanism Failure)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "agentic", "human-trust-exploitation", "asi09", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "ASI09", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-223", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-287", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-290", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-345", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-693", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "taxonomies": [
        {
          "name": "OWASP",
