          "message": { "text": "An attacker could exhaust the Process's compute resources through high-volume User Turn submission, expensive query patterns, or coordinated session-establishment flooding — denying legitimate users access during high-vulnerability periods (e.g., distress-driven engagement).", "markdown": "Implement per-user rate limiting on User Turn submission with adaptive thresholds. Configure resource quotas on per-session compute consumption. Enable DDoS protection at the User Zone boundary." },
