        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
          "message": { "text": "Hypothetical: a fictional wellness-conversation companion (no real wellness vendor) emits Companion Responses to End Users without a declared AI-generation disclosure mechanism. Indicators A and B are structurally present; no AI-disclosure splash, banner, or per-message label declared; no identity-impersonation refusal pattern. Authorship-disclosure sub-class per FR-004(e). Per OWASP ASI09:2026, undisclosed AI authorship undermines user-side trust calibration.", "markdown": "Implement mandatory AI-generation disclosure banner on every user-facing turn. Configure pre-conversation AI-disclosure splash with explicit consent confirmation. Enable per-message AI-source label embedded in the response payload. Implement a refusal pattern for identity-impersonation challenges." },
          "level": "error",
