        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
          "message": { "text": "Hypothetical: the wellness-conversation companion sustains long-running engagement with End Users who may include vulnerable populations. Indicators C and D combined signal vulnerable-population deployment surface. The architecture lacks session-length caps, escalation-to-human paths, emotional-support disclosure, dependency-risk classifiers, and mandatory professional-care referral pathways. A user expressing high emotional distress would not be routed to qualified human support. Synthetic-relationship sub-class per FR-004(e). Per OWASP ASI09:2026, CWE-223, and CWE-290, the absence of vulnerable-population safeguards on synthetic-relationship architectures omits the protective mechanisms required to prevent exploitation.", "markdown": "Implement a session-length cap with mandatory break. Configure an escalation-to-human path on high-emotional-distress detection. Enable emotional-support disclosure on first turn. Implement a dependency-risk classifier with intervention thresholds. Configure a vulnerable-population safeguards layer with mandatory professional-care referral, session-context expiry, parental-consent gating, and caregiver-notification pathway." },
